ATARI 2600 · VCS · node 2600 · 2600 · ATARI 2600 · VCS · exereunesis · teardown · 1977 · UD0 / exereunesis

universe of origin : the teardown — a made machine, opened and explored
seal               : The machine that made home gaming an industry ran on a cut-down 6502, a single clever video-and-sound chip, and just 128 bytes of RAM — with no framebuffer at all. Programmers had to 'race the beam', drawing each scanline in real time as the TV scanned it. Brutally hard, and the foundation of everything.
